<p>As i know so far clion does not support makefile so instead of makefile uses cMakeList.txt. The problem that i face is the following: I am trying to add the -lm option in c compiler but does not work.</p>  <p>For example if i compile the program from terminal i have to add <code>-lm</code> option for c compiler because in my source i use <code>math.h</code> library.</p>  <pre><code>Terminal:gcc isPrime.c -lm -o runprime </code></pre>  <p>This is working from the terminal but how i can do the equivalent in clion using CMakelist.txt</p>  <pre><code>My CMakelist.txt: cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.2) project(epl601Ex1)  set(CMAKE_C_FLAGS "--Wall -lm")  set(SOURCE_FILES isPrime.c) add_executable(PrimeProj ${SOURCE_FILES} ) </code></pre>  <p>Thanks, Joni</p>